Preheat the oven to 350 degrees Fahrenheit.
Combine flour, brown sugar, oats (if using), salt, and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Pour in melted butter and mix until crumbly.
Place all the filling ingredients in a large bowl.
Transfer the apple mixture to a baking dish.
Bake for 40 minutes or until the top is golden brown and crisp.
Pour some vanilla custard on the side and garnish with extra cinnamon.
Enjoy!
